                            <comment id="12622969" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2008 18:40:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Checks if the family is null. The rest was already taken care of.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622970" author="stack" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2008 18:41:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tim Sell just found same issue over in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-657&quot; title=&quot;InvalidColumnNameException not passed through to Thrift interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-657&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-657&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622973" author="stack" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2008 18:45:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it should throw... NoSuchColumnFamilyException&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;11:44&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;	&amp;lt;st^ack&amp;gt;	This is a DoNotRetryIOException&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;11:44&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;	&amp;lt;st^ack&amp;gt;	Then we don&apos;t retry it.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;11:44&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;	&amp;lt;st^ack&amp;gt;	Fixes tim&apos;s issue then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622975" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2008 18:51:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It already does in HRegion.checkColumn, my NPE was just hiding it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12622980" author="stack" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2008 19:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right J-D.  I see it down in localput.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
